The paper discusses a random feature scheme inspired by convolutional neural networks and kernels, which are commonly used in machine learning for image processing and computer vision tasks. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and social and information networks (cs.SI) which often deal with similar topics.
